history.content: IMO it's doable if you don't have many other major commitments, your other classes (if any) are very easy, and you're decently comfortable around lower-level programming and C (bonus if you know C++ for 15); a good benchmark could be how comfortable/enjoyable 61C was for you. 161 and 194-15 are both low-medium workload classes. 162 I'm sure you've heard is a lot of work but with no other major timesinks it's doable if challenging.
